		<title>05EMPLOYMENT</title>
		<content> Children over the age of thirteen can 
 find occasional employment in         
 bush-beating and seasonal picking of  
 crops such as potatoes.               
                                       
 In Thornton Watlass there is a family 
 building firm who employ local labour.
 They have built or renovated several  
 houses in the village. The family name
 is reflected in the names of houses,  
 e.g. "Appledale", and in the name of  
 the small development called Dale     
 Close. Three generations of Dales are 
 at present among the employees.       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
